# Responsive Dialog / Modal Shell

## Required shell components

Module components **never** use raw `Dialog` or `Drawer` directly. Always compose with:

| Component | Source | Role |
|---|---|---|
| `ResponsiveSheet` | `@/components/patterns` | Root wrapper — renders `Dialog` on desktop, `Drawer` (bottom sheet) on mobile |
| `ResponsiveSheetContent` | `@/components/patterns` | Content wrapper with scroll/safe-area handling |
| `ModalHeading` | `@/components/patterns` | Title + description block |
| `DialogFooter` | `@/components/ui` | Button row (Cancel + Submit) |

## Minimal structure

```tsx
<ResponsiveSheet open={open} onOpenChange={onOpenChange}>
  <ResponsiveSheetContent className="max-w-full sm:max-h-[min(90vh,46rem)] sm:overflow-y-auto sm:max-w-lg md:max-w-3xl">
    <ModalHeading title={t.feature.dialogTitle} description={<p>{t.feature.dialogDescription}</p>} />
    <form onSubmit={...}>
      {/* fields */}
      <DialogFooter>
        <Button type="button" variant="outline" onClick={() => setOpen(false)}>
          {t.common.cancel}
        </Button>
        <Button type="submit">{t.common.save}</Button>
      </DialogFooter>
    </form>
  </ResponsiveSheetContent>
</ResponsiveSheet>
```

## Standard content sizing

Use `className="max-w-full sm:max-h-[min(90vh,46rem)] sm:overflow-y-auto sm:max-w-lg md:max-w-3xl"` on `ResponsiveSheetContent` for dialogs with forms. Adjust `max-w-*` breakpoints if the form is wider (e.g. multi-column layouts).

## Accessibility

- Call `useId()` **once** per dialog component; use as an ID prefix for every form field: `${formId}-title`, `${formId}-amount`, etc.
- Set `aria-invalid={!!err}` on every input control (`Input`, `SelectTrigger`, `VndAmountInput`, `MonthYearPicker`).
- Assign `id={errId}` to each `FieldError`; set `aria-describedby={err ? errId : undefined}` on the control.

## onOpenChange cleanup

When the sheet closes (`onOpenChange(false)`), reset `editing` state to `null` so the dialog reverts to create mode if re-opened:

```tsx
onOpenChange={(v) => {
  setOpen(v)
  if (!v) setEditing(null)
}}
```

